parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the factory-installed stereo amplifier can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to damage to the vehicle and risk to the occupants.
symptoms: Popping and clicking sounds from the speakers
crackling noise
amplifier failure
and in some cases
a fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Repair Parts for Amplifier Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of repair parts for the amplifier recall can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to fires or other hazards.
symptoms: Dealership unable to honor recall due to no parts available
parts not received
and no estimated time for part availability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioner compressor can cause damage to the engine and surrounding components.
symptoms: Explosion of the air conditioner compressor
scrap metal all over the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy during a crash
despite meeting the deployment threshold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted airbag deployment can cause distractions, loss of control, and accidents, as well as injuries from the deploying airbag.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without a crash or impact
or deploy excessively
causing damage to the vehicle or injury to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light stays on
the brakes fail to engage
the vehicle continues to roll forward during panic stops
the brakes are soft or spongy
the master cylinder is leaking
the high-pressure hose is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The master cylinder is leaking
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The airbags do not deploy during a collision
the driver and passenger airbags fail to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission shifts noisily and hard
even after new transmission fluid has been installed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause various problems, including battery drain, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The battery goes dead after a short period
the center console/armrest breaks
the coffee holder will not return to its stored/locked position
the rear power window on the driver's side sometimes does not work from the driver's seat.
